05/03/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Belgrade District Court spokeswoman Ivana Ramic said on Tuesday (March 4th) that prosecutors are launching an inquiry into the fire at the US Embassy during last month's protests against Kosovo's independence. One man has been arrested for arson and theft, stemming from the February 21st attack. A 21-year old student, Zoran Vujovic, died in the fire. Last Friday, police filed criminal charges against 80 people allegedly involved in attacks on the US and other embassies in Belgrade. (B92, Tanjug, FoNet, RTS, AP, AFP - 04/03/08)
